-- HIV Infections Fell 35% in South Africa From 2002-2008, Sunday Times Says
-- Vernon Wessels
-- 2010-06-20T08:52:54Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-20/south-africa-s-new-hiv-infections-decline-35-the-sunday-times-reports.html

          
          
             New HIV infections in South Africa 
dropped by 35 percent between 2002 and 2008, the Sunday Times 
said, citing a study.  
 There was a 60 percent decline in infections among people 
aged 15 to 24, indicating that the countryâ€™s prevention 
campaigns, promotion of condom use and HIV tests were helping, 
the Johannesburg-based newspaper said, citing the study, 
entitled SA National HIV Prevalence, Incidence, Behavior and 
Communications Survey: A Turning Tide Among Teenagers?  
          
          


  


        